******
[2] Pakistan - new case WPV1 (December 2018) - media report
Date: Thu 10 Jan 2019
Source: The News [edited]
https://www.thenews.com.pk/latest/417131-polio-case-reported-in-lakki-marwat


A polio case has been reported in Lakki Marwat district of Khyber Pakhtunhwa [province], an official Twitter handle reported.

"Polio case has been reported from Lakki Marwat, Khyber Pakhtunkhwa. Total number of polio cases in Pakistan in 2018 is at 9. Vaccinating all children in every campaign is critical to attain full immunity against the virus and to #endpolio in #Pakistan," End Polio tweeted.

Babar Atta, focal person to Prime Minister Imran Khan, confirmed that another polio case was reported from district Lakki Marwat in Khyber Pakhtunkhwa.

He said that samples of the child were collected during December 2018; therefore, the case belongs to 2018 polio case tally.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[As this case is listed in the End Polio Pakistan tally of confirmed cases, we should expect to see this case reported in the weekly WHO/GPEI weekly updates in the coming weeks. This will raise the total number of polio cases reported by Pakistan in 2018 to 9 (see http://www.endpolio.com.pk/polioin-pakistan/polio-cases-in-provinces), and the global total for 2018 will increase to 30.

Additional information from a Dawn article (that was published while I was writing this moderator comment!) mentions the case is a 16-month-old girl from the Marmundu Azam area of district Lakki Marwat, and that the girl had onset of paralysis on 10 Dec 2018. The Pakistani National Institute of Health confirmed the case today [Thu 10 Jan 2019] (https://www.dawn.com/news/1456707/polio-case-surfaces-in-khyber-pakhtunkhwas-lakki-marwat-district).

Checking prior reports, the most recent positive environmental sample from Khyber Pakhtunkhwa province was from Bannu district and was reported in Poliomyelitis update (61): global (Nigeria), comment on social media 20181221.6217827. (Other reports of positive environmental samples from Khyber Pakhtunkhwa Province do not mention the district where the sample was taken). The most recent confirmed case in Pakistan in Lakki Marwat district, Khyber Pakhtunkhwa province, had a date of onset of paralysis on 21 Aug 2017.

A map of Khyber Pukhtunkhwa province showing districts can be found at http://pamirtours.pk/maps/PD%20Maps/KPK_districts_map_2.jpg. Lakki Marwat is located in the southern portion of the province, bordering with both North and South Waziristan districts, which are in the known endemic regions of the country. - Mod.MPP]
